{panel:title=Atlassian Update – 1 April 2021|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ebf2f9 | titleBGColor=#ebf2f9 | bgColor=#ffffff}
Hi everyone,

Despite this update being on April 1st, I want to assure followers this _isn't_ an April fools joke! 

Thanks for voting and commenting on this suggestion. Your feedback is key to helping us understand how you use Confluence and Jira so we can continue improving your experience. 

We've heard from a lot of you that one of the main reasons you want this feature is that you are doing project status reporting in Jira. Over the last few months, we've been looking into how make project status reporting a much more enjoyable experience for everyone and help scale project communication within an organisation. We'd love to hear your feedback about this as we have a Beta which is free for Cloud customers who already use Jira and/or Confluence. All you have to to is sign-up here: https://www.atlassian.com/software/team-central

Let us know what you think by hitting "Feedback" in product or feel free to reach out to me directly smansour@atlassian.com. 

Regards,
Sherif Mansour
Product Manager, Atlassian
{panel}


